Package: wgsHLAfiltR
Title: Whole Genome Sequence HLA Filter
Version: 0.2.0
Authors@R: c(person("Steven", "Mack", email = "steven.mack@ucsf.edu", role = c("aut", "cre")),
             person("Tasneem","Yusufali", email="tasneem.yusufali@ucsf.edu", role="aut"))
Description: Extracts reads that map to the genomic coordinates of the classical Human Leukocyte Antigen (HLA) Loci (HLA-A, -C, -B, -DRB1, -DRB3/4/5, -DQA1, -DQB1, -DPA1 and -DPB1) from fastq.gz files, using hg19 coordinates, and writes, new HLA-reads-only, fastq.gz files. This package includes 132.3Mb of data required for read alignment, and requires bowtie2 installation in the local system.
Depends: R (>= 4.0.0)
License: GPL (>= 3)
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 7.1.1
Imports: stringr, methods
Suggests: knitr, rmarkdown
VignetteBuilder: knitr
